"开启后同步 iPhone 与 Apple Watch 支持的数据。" = "Syncs supported data between iPhone and Apple Watch when enabled.";
"用于同一 Apple ID 下的多设备漫游。" = "Used for roaming across devices under the same Apple ID.";
"同步与备份说明正文" = "Database snapshots manually export or restore .elsbackup files, useful for moving devices, cross-device disaster recovery, and manual backups.\n\nStartup protection only guards against SQLite database corruption. When enabled, each launch asynchronously creates one local restore point. After the new restore point passes validation, the previous one is deleted, so only one recoverable version is kept. If corruption is detected on launch, the app asks before restoring from it.\n\niCloud Roaming Sync is the recommended seamless path. Keep it enabled under the same Apple ID and the app will automatically upload and fetch supported data so iPhone, iPad, and Apple Watch stay as aligned as possible.\n\nApple Watch nearby sync is for manually reconciling data between iPhone and Apple Watch. If both sides did not enable iCloud Sync from the start, their databases may already have diverged like separate histories, and direct merging is not reliable. Database overwrite lets you choose, for chat, configuration, and memory, whether to keep the iPhone or Apple Watch copy; the other side's matching database will be replaced. Before overwriting, you can send important single conversations to the other device from the conversation list.\n\nThe legacy merge engine remains available manually, but it may bring back providers, settings, or conversations that were deleted on only one side. Use it only when you accept that risk.";
